Fans are sending congratulatory messages to singer Wahu and her husband David Mathenge, who are expecting baby number three. The mother of two announced her pregnancy in a cute dance video with her family. In the video posted on her social media, Wahu and her family were jamming to their new song, 'Deep'. She said they are expecting a new member in their family. Wahu and Nameless have two daughters, Tumiso who is 15 years, while Nyakio will be turning seven years in August. Nameless also shared the video on his social media account. "Naona it's about time tuongezeee.. ama. Grateful moment." Back in 2020, Nameless told Word Is he wanted another baby. "Siwezi mind a boy now that I have two girls, but we are still under discussions."